-- int_customer_channels_deduped.sql
-- Deduplicate to one channel per customer using latest attribution
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT customer_id, channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- int_transactions_enriched.sql
-- Enrich transactions with store city information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.store_id,
        t.amount,
        t.transaction_date,
        COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_stores') }} s
        ON s.store_id = t.store_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

```sql
-- fct_revenue_by_channel_city.sql
-- Aggregate revenue by attribution channel and store city
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        COALESCE(cc.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel,
        te.city,
        te.amount,
        te.transaction_id,
        te.customer_id
    FROM {{ ref('int_transactions_enriched') }} te
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_customer_channels_deduped') }} cc
        ON cc.customer_id = te.customer_id
)
SELECT
    channel,
    city,
    SUM(amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(DISTINCT transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM source
GROUP BY channel, city
ORDER BY total_revenue DESC
